        "text": "* Naturally enforces a [[Modular programming|modular]] structure.<ref name=\"martinfowler\"/>\n* Lends itself to a [[continuous delivery]] software development process. A change to a small part of the application only requires one or a small number of services to be rebuilt and redeployed.<ref name=\"martinfowler\"/>\n* Adheres to principles such as [[Service granularity principle|fine-grained]] [[software interface|interface]]s (to independently deployable services), business-driven development (e.g. [[domain-driven design]]), [[IDEAL]] [[cloud application]] architectures, [[Polyglot (computing)|polyglot programming]] and persistence, lightweight [[Container (abstract data type)|container]] deployment, decentralized continuous delivery, and [[DevOps]] with holistic service monitoring.[https://www.ifs.hsr.ch/index.php?id=15266&L=4 IFS: Microservices Resources and Positions]\n* Provides characteristics that are beneficial to scalability.[https://arxiv.org/pdf/1704.04173.pdf Microservices: Migration of a Mission Critical System][https://arxiv.org/pdf/1702.07149.pdf Microservices: How To Make Your Application Scale]"
